
This library currently does not build under GCC because as the new documentation
states, GCC does not allow you to smash a square peg into a square hole of the
wrong type.  This will be fixed eventually.  The build still works with CLANG.

To buile type

    export CC=clang
    make

This will build thelibrary which can then be installed with

   make install

which (in Gentoo at least) will install the .so file as 

    /usr/local/lib64/libuCurses.so.1.0 

with an associated symlink 

    /usr/local/lib64/libuCurses.so

You may need to run ldconfig for your applications to be able to build
against this library. 
